**Update on July 29, 2016: Sammy is still searching for his special someone, in foster care in Toronto**

Meet Sammy! Sammy was found as a stray, and was picked up by a volunteer from the rescue and made his way to Canada last fall.  Sammy is a lot of dog packed into a solid, slightly dachshund-y body. He's energetic and super intelligent, and he can be lots of fun! He loves lots of physical and mental stimulation. In his current home, he frequently goes on runs and walks in the ravine. He's a great hiking companion and would love something like a scenting or recreational agility class!

Sammy has been evaluated by a professional trainer, and she describes him as âa big working dog in a small dogâs body,â and he needs the right kind of family -- one that is committed to working with him on an ongoing basis, that has a lot of patience, and will provide the leadership he needs to reach his full potential.  Sammy is not an aggressive dog, but can be dominant and therefore requires a human with dog handling experience as he is inclined to guard his resources, toys and beloved humans, especially in his home environment. He can be reactive on leash around other dogs, and he has bitten when he felt his territory was encroached upon, but he has flourished in foster care with training and guidance.

We are looking for an experienced guardian or guardians, and a home with no small children. A home with another canine may work, a female is preferred, and it would be contingent upon a successful trial period.  Despite these challenges, this guy is a wonderful, comical and engaging little dude, who and would make a loving and very rewarding companion in the right home.  And did we mention he's smart as a whip? With that enormous head, how could he not be?

A Delcie & Lilly update: If you like hounds, youâll love the âHoundie Girlsâ. They have been in our home as fosters since November 2013. While they are around 14 years old, they didnât âget the memoâ that they are senior dogs. They love a good walk, just like their 5 year old foster sister. In fact, Delcie bounces around like a puppy whenever the leash is brought out. They live for their walks and enjoy backyard time, although preferably with a sweater during a winter like the last one! In our home the houndies are the 2nd half to a foursome, and get along well with our two dogs, one senior and one youngster. They arenât keen on public âmeet-upsâ at the dog park or HBR events. Like many floppy eared breeds, the girls are plagued by chronic ear issues. Regular cleaning and strategic upkeep seems to maintain their comfort, but the amount of scarring makes for a chronic condition. They are not keen on ear cleaning or nail trimming. The âHoundiesâ maintain their hounding ways, engaging in the odd sampling of garbage if available and love table scraps, taking advantage of any opportunity. They enjoy engaging in regular âchoir practiceâ, howling in unison with foster dad, and make for a great alarm system in the house! The ladies would prefer to lounge on the furniture, but the foster parents encourage dog beds, and the girls oblige. âHounding Hourâ can happen anywhere, they are happiest when with their people, relaxing or walking. These two ladies have personality plus and are truly lovable, Lilly waves with her paw when you come to talk to her, Delcie wags the tip of her tail when spoken (or sung) to. Perhaps you would like a âHounding Hourâ at your house? Delcie and Lilly would be happy to join you.

"Hi there. My name is Hope. I am up to date with vaccines and spayed. I am a 1 year old Mastiff X (foster mom says Husky!) who for whatever reason, landed myself in a shelter. Thankfully, Homeward Bound rescued me and gave me a chance to find my forever family. My foster mom says that I am a big cuddle bug who will actually wrap my paws around you and close my eyes to give you as big a hug as possible. I am always at my foster humans' feet and love to be around them as much as possible. Given that I am part Husky, I LOVE the outdoors! I love to play and run and chase my foster brother around the yard. I am quite the jumper and runner given my lean physique and "mush dog" genes and would certainly need a high, fenced in yard to avoid me jumping the fence and getting lost. I am house trained but sometimes get so excited when my foster humans come home that I accidentally piddle a little bit. Sorry...I am still quite young and excitable. This will change as I mature I'm sure of it. I am a little nervous when first meeting new dogs and can get a little agitated if I am introduced too quickly and not given time to adjust. I do not bite but will certainly let other dogs know that they are bothering me and to back off. I do like my own space and would prefer to be around humans rather than other dogs. I definitely do not like dominant male dogs and would prefer a home with a more submissive/laid back/smaller dog(s). My foster brother is that kind of dog and we play and cuddle together all the time. I can be a bit whiny if I am left alone. This is also my cue for "I need to go to the bathroom". I am crate trained and do just fine in a crate. My foster mom tells me I have an excellent recall and am doing fantastic with leash training (she says I'm much smarter than my foster brother but I'm not allowed to tell him she said that). I am continuing to learn manners and recently learned how to "roll over" in minutes, but only for peanut butter. My foster parents are working with me and say I am showing improvements every day-not that I have bad manners I just haven't had much stability and training. As long as I keep getting peanut butter, I will show as many improvements as possible! I am very attached to my 16 year old foster sister (mainly because she lets me sleep in her big comfy bed). Just so I have the best opportunity possible at finding my forever home, I would probably be better off in a home with children over 12 as I have not been around small children to know whether I like them or not. What else can I say...come meet me for a hug :)"

*CROSS POST THIS IS NOT AN HBR DOG PLEASE SEE CONTACT INFO AT BOTTOMHi my name is Maggie but sometime my mom calls me moo moo. I am a sweet and loving 2 1/2 year old Old English Bulldog. I love to go on walks and play a good game of tug of war with my rope, but that doesn't mean I don't love snuggling up with a good movie too, cause I really do. I also love.....well everyone, but my mom says that because I'm a tank I'm too rough with babies and toddlers. I don't mean to hurt them I just want to give them lots of slobbery wet kisses. I love to play with my fur brother too, but he's a lot older than me and gets grumpy easily and sometimes I hurt him. So a younger dog for me to play with would be great. I do have allergies but nobody can figure out to what, so sometimes I breakout in a rash, but it's nothing a nice warm bath with baking soda and some benadryl can't fix. And I do love a good bath. My mom thinks I was a golden retriever in my past life cause I love water so much. Maggie is located in Bowmanville please email sweet_74@rogers.com or call (905) 244-7887

Hey HBR Fans,Murphy here .. look at me!! I look like a 4 -legged dog!!! It's going to take some time to get used to having 4 legs!! I will need to build some new muscle so I can walk and run properly on it, but foster mom says I'm up for the challenge! She is sooooo proud of me! Foster mom says I can only wear it three times a day for 20 minutes at a time for now. Just like any kind of exercise, it takes time to get use to and work up some muscle in my shoulder that I never had before.I still have a long way to go, but I'm taking it one paw at a timewink emoticonThe AMAZING people at HBR are still raising money to cover the cost of my prosthetic, so if you could spare a couple dollars to go towards my new leg, I would REALLY appreciate it.You can visit www.homewardboundrescue.ca for ways to donate. You can also go online at www.canadahelps.org and select Homeward Bound Rescue.Murphy is being fostered in Barrie

Hello future family! My name is Alpha but my foster mom says my name should be Zen becauseof my calm nature and because I like to do yoga poses. I love joining my foster family on longwalks, shopping at pet stores, playing with my stuffy chicken or just sitting on the porchwatching the world go by. I love to be with them all the time and would do best in a foreverhome where I have company most of the time. I am happy to be active, cuddle on the couch orsit quietly beside you.I like to go out with them to explore the world. I am comfortable and well behaved when visitingfriends, in crowds at markets, walking along busy streets or hiking trails in the forest. I love tomeet and greet both people and dogs and I am always complemented on my lovely doggymanners and good looks. People have mistaken me for the dog in Disneyâs Homeward Bound.They think Iâm a celebrity!I know my basic commands and I am a quick learner. My foster mom crate trained me in 1week! I love my airline crate and often sit in it quietly waiting for food or to see if the treat fairyleft me a little something. I will do anything for a bit of food!If you are looking for a quiet, well mannered, super smart and loving doggy, Iâm your boy!DUE TO MY SIZE I WILL ONLY GO TO A HOME WITH CHILDREN OVER THE AGE OF 12ALPHA IS CURRENTLY ON PHENOBARBITAL FOR EPILEPSY *Alpha is being fostered in Petawawa*

*ADOPTION PENDING*Hi! My name is Bob, I am a 6 years young, sweet, shy boy who loves to be around my people and fur brothers and sisters. I love to run and sometimes even escape the house to go on adventures! I am gentle with everyone and have never been aggressive towards my humans. I don't really like barking and I never go to the bathroom inside!I do have some special quirks from my puppy mill days, but with a routine these seem to not come about so often. My foster mom says that when I am upset I bump things with my nose off of tables and I pace. I just need some comforting and then I stop. I also require medication to help me with my anxiety which helps.I have lived with other dogs and cats and sometimes I even enjoy a good cat chase but I never hurt them.BOB IS BEING FOSTERED IN AJAX

Hi Paz here, I have been around for quite awhile settling into the foster life but I think its about time I find a family to call my own! Here is a bit about me, then you can tell me all about you :) I was surrendered into HBR care as my person could no longer look after me (this took alot courage for him to do) I am a stunning 3 year old Boxer mix (likely Mastiff) who is 100lbs of pure love ..if I don't say so myselfI love people of all sizes, dogs of all sizes and even his feline friends. I have been fully vetted by the nice people at HBR (thank you) Now for my quirks (we all have them) - I am very strong on leash and require an experienced owner- I think I would do best in a home with children over the age of 12 (because I am so strong)- I would need an owner that doesn't mind working on my leash skillsIf I sound like the guy for you, I would love to hear all about you and your quirks.. remember I am really looking for my furever home!Love PazPaz is being fostered in Port Perry

description.$t:
Hi, I'm Precious. Well, I AM cherished here at the EHS, but that's not what I mean â Precious is my name! I'm a slimmer, longer haired version of my sister Coco. I'm as friendly as can be, and love having my long fur combed as I sit next to you on my blankets that are laid out on my various couches. I am easy going and get along with almost everybody, people and cats alike. Coco and I are furry couch potatoes who would keep you company as you read a book, or watch some television. We require some medication, but are otherwise very low maintenance. Come on by the EHS for a casual, care free visit with me and my sister Coco! We hope to see you soon! 

Make it count, save a life, adopt a mature cat.

Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter. 

To make an appointment to meet Precious and CoCo or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301, email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com, or fill out our new, easy online cat adoption form at http://etobicokehumanesociety.com/adoption-process/.

description.$t:
Oh hello! I'm Coco the calico. I'm twelve years young, and perhaps a little larger than I'd like to be, but my heart is just as big, and so is my couch! Older cats like my sister Precious and I are easily over looked. So please give us a moment of your time, and we will show you our extraordinarily friendly natures. The two of us would love nothing more than go together (as we are bonded) to a forever and loving home where we can cuddle up to you on the couch day after day, while you pat our heads and we share our contented purrs. We are tame well behaved girls with easy going temperaments. We are purrfect! And we would love to find the perfect people to accept us and love us no matter what! We'd love to meet you, so swing by and give us a friendly hello! 

Make it count, save a life, adopt a mature cat.

Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter. 

To make an appointment to meet CoCo and Precious or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301, email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com, or fill out our new, easy online cat adoption form at http://etobicokehumanesociety.com/adoption-process/.

First things first, ladies and gentlemen, I am not a female My long, soft, luscious hair seems to dissuade people of the notion that I'm male, but believe it, folks! And my brother, with whom I am bonded, is also a male, despite his name, Sasha. I am extremely easy going as I lounge on the computer's keyboard, the top of the fridge,  the windowsill, or wedge myself into the back of a desk. I do go wild for my catnip sausages! I love to lick and chew them, and bat them around, and after that I usually lay contentedly outstretched on my back, awaiting a few belly rubs. We do require daily medication, but that's just like some people! We are pretty good about taking our pills. If you are ready for lounge happy cats, give my brother Sasha and I a visit here at the EHS. We will be wandering the reception area, waiting to greet you upon your arrival. 

Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter 

To make an appointment to meet this wonderful cat or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

Good day to you all! I am Sasha, protector of the reception desk here at EHS. I am an affectionate, carefree 8 year old cat who enjoys chasing laser pointers and feathers, not to mention finding  incredibly small, but delightfully satisfying, sleeping spots around the shelter. If we fits, we sits! When I am not sleeping, I love to peer in and look at the kittens in their room - a room that used to be Angel's and mine as a matter of fact . I've heard rumors that some believe I want that room back, but I'll never tell. I've enjoyed my stay here at the EHS for the past year and half as I get to meet all the folks who come in, and get fawned over for my cute face that's too small for my body; but it's truly time that Angel and I found a home to call our own.

Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter

To make an appointment to meet this wonderful cat or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

I am very scared right now, having been left in a cardboard box with my sister and brother at the doorstep of EHS â not a great way to start off my 6 month old life, but I know I will mature into a very sweet cat and live up to my namesake. Just like syrup takes time to develop, so do I. If you donât mind helping a scared cat transform into a confident cat who will appreciate you for taking a chance on her, then please donât hesitate to start up a friendship with me. Iâll be here at the EHS, just pop on by.

Hi there! My name is Chloe. I am a very sweet two and a half year old grey and white kitty. I grew up in a concrete warehouse, which is where I developed problems with a tear duct on my right eye. It's no big deal; I just need someone to wipe away my tears once a day. At EHS, I'm in much better conditions but I'll probably be crying of happiness when someone decides to take me to my forever home. Even though I haven't had the best time growing up, I'm very affectionate and love attention. I'm new here so I'm still a bit shy but just hanging out with me is enough to melt a few hearts. So if you want a sweet little cat that would love to curl up with you on a boring afternoon, I'm just the cat for you!

To make an appointment to meet this wonderful cat or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

Hello, my name is Rocky. I am a very nice 8 year old boy who just wants to live in a nice home. I was found in front of a pet store with my best buddy Rambo. We are really close and make each other feel safe. We were taken in by EHS and are now looking for a place to call our own. I love attention and although I may be very scared at first, it doesn't take me a long time to warm up.  I have badly matted fur on my back and some dental problems.  Like my namesake however, I'm a fighter. I refuse to let these little things bother me. But I'm getting all cleaned up and before I know it, I'll seem like I'm 2. I can't wait to have a home where Rambo and I can relax.
 
Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter. 

To make an appointment to meet these wonderful cats or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

Hi, how ya doin'? My name is Rambo and I am a nice, soft, 2 year old boy. I live with my buddy Rocky. We've been through a lot together. There was this one time where some man picked us up when we were living outside and he brought us to EHS. I was really scared. But I had Rocky so it wasn't too bad. I have a hunger for life, and for wet food. You would think I've never eaten. Rocky and I are real nice and if you are nice to us, we'll love you. I love when people scratch under my chin and feed me. I'm not too hard to please. But it would be nice to live somewhere where Rocky and I will be spoiled with love. 

Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter. 

To make an appointment to meet this wonderful cat or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

Hey there, I'm Cece. I am 6 years old and I love people. I was dropped off in a carrier outside in the rain. I was there overnight so you would see why I'm a bit shy. As bad as my way of getting here was, I am very friendly. I always greet my visitors with some head butts and a purr whenever someone walks in. I'm not too fond of the cats that pass by but when people pass by, all I want is for them so come and see me. I'm looking for a home with a nice family. I just really want to be your cuddly lap cat.
Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter. 

To make an appointment to meet this wonderful cat or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

Hi. My name is Quincy. I am 3 years old. I was rescued from a high kill shelter and I'm in pretty rough shape. Before arriving at the shelter, I was attacked by the other cats a lot so I have some battle scars. Despite that, I'm super gentle and friendly. I'll always greet you with a nice meow. I really love when people visit and come pet me. I may look a little beat up but I'll get better. When I'm feeling better, I can't wait to go to some lovely people in their loving home. It would be nice to know what a family is. If you want to meet me, I'd love to see you!


Our adoption fee  includes: up to date vaccinations, microchip, and spay/ neuter. 

To make an appointment to meet this wonderful cat or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

Hey there Delilah, what's it like at the society? 
Well, it's still pretty scary, but I'm getting used to it fast. I came from the same place as Amanda and I was in the same place. I was on death row as well. I'm not as outgoing as the other cats but I'm still very sweet. Slow and steady wins the race, right? It'll take a little extra effort to help me be comfortable around people but everyone says I'm doing well. I really love being pet, as long as you are nice and gentle, I'll let you pet me for hours. I just need a family that will help my colours shine! I swear that once you take the time to get to know me, I'm pretty great!

Hi. My name is Soria. I am 2 years old and I'm the proud mom of 4 beautiful kittens. They are old enough to live on their own so I am looking to do the same. I'm still quite shy, I was so frazzled for a while that I really didn't know what to do with myself. I am a little more comfortable now, but it'll take time for me to be completely comfy. I know not everyone wants a cat that is shy or scared, but that doesn't mean that I don't deserve a home. I may be shy but I'm really nice once you get to know me. I just need a little extra time. Please try to find room in your home and your heart for a young cat looking for a home.

To make an appointment to meet this wonderful cat or for more information please contact the Etobicoke Humane Society at: 416-249-6100 EXT:301 or email: cats@etobicokehumanesociety.com

Hello, my name is Patchy. I am a 7-year-old boy. I was with my old family for 7 years but, unfortunately, I had to leave because they developed allergies to me. Being brought to the shelter is a scary experience for me. Please don't use my personality right now to judge how I really am. After my family gave me up, I don't have the greatest trust in people. If you take the time to help me get back to the real me, I would love to show you the sweet, gentle and adorable boy that my family fell in love with in the first place.

Hi! My name is Ryder and I am a 2 year old Lab/Husky mix. When I first meet people I am a little nervous and shy, especially if they are men, but once I get a chance to know them I really warm up. I arrived at the shelter because someone abandoned me.  I do not understand why. All the volunteers at EHS say I'm so sweet. I may get a little howly, it's the Husky in me, so I would not do well in an apartment or condo. I hope that I will find a patient human that will give me the time to come out of my shell and let me enjoy being a dog.

He is a wonderful dog waiting patiently for a loving family.

For more information on the EHS adoption process please visit our website, or for further details on Cisco please email mgy.ehs@gmail.com.

Teddy is currently in foster so please email jleung.ehs@gmail.com if you would like to set up a time to meet him.

Hi there! My name is Teddy, but you can call me Teddy Bear because I am  so cute. I am a 6 year old shih-tzu. I love people and will happily wag my tail for you if you come and meet me. Everyone says I am a real cuddle-bug. I enjoy walks but after that, I'm happy to sit with you and read a good book or watch some TV. I want you all to myself so if you have another pet, I am sorry but I prefer not to share you. If you teach me, I will not mind having doggy friends to play with sometimes though. I sleep in my crate and I am a big boy so no need to worry about me 'going' inside the house. Come and meet me!

Sometimes it's love at first sight. That was certainly the case for Little Miss Sunshine and Boots, who acted like long lost lovers from the moment they first saw each other, and have been inseparable ever since. They first laid eyes on each other when Little Miss Sunshine arrived at Boots' foster home for assessment after being rescued from a colony. Little Miss Sunshine was in a recovery cage and Boots came in the room to investigate. As soon as they saw each other Boots came right up to Sunshine's cage and she pressed her face into his. Her foster mom let Sunshine out of her recovery cage, and she ran to Boots for a head-butt, and never looked back. Today they do absolutely everything together - even walking side by side and leaning against each other when they walk to another room looking for their foster parents or their next meal.

This adorable twosome isn't just affectionate with each other - they love their foster parents too. Little Miss Sunshine loves being pet and sitting on your lap, and has an unrivaled 'elevator butt'! Boots adores being brushed and can spend hours purring and circling your legs and flopping against your feet for attention.  Neither are big fans of being picked up and held, but they make up for it with the incredible amount of attention they will give you 'at ground level'. Since they both spent at least a few years fending for themselves on the streets, they are jumpy around new people, loud noises, and sudden unexpected movements, so they should go to a fairly quiet home without children. But once you've won their hearts (which is pretty easy with food and treats!), this cuddly duo will never leave you alone. 

They are both in great health, but Boots is FIV positive - a legacy of spending almost his entire life living on the streets. He adores indoor life, with its constant supply of attention, food, and toys, but endearingly still hasn't figured out how to drink out of a water bowl, after so many years of having to dip his paw into puddles to get water! Both Little Miss Sunshine and Boots love other cats - especially Boots, who is built like a tank, but has the heart of a teddy bear and the mew of a kitten. Little Miss Sunshine and Boots are a heartwarming and wonderful pair of cats, and watching them together is guaranteed to bring a smile on even the darkest day. Don't believe us? Her foster mom let Sunshine out of her recovery cage, and she ran to Boots for a head-butt, and never looked back. Today they do absolutely everything together - even walking side by side and leaning against each other when they walk to another room looking for their foster parents or their next meal.

This adorable twosome isn't just affectionate with each other - they love their foster parents too. Little Miss Sunshine loves being pet and sitting on your lap, and has an unrivaled 'elevator butt'! Boots adores being brushed and can spend hours purring and circling your legs and flopping against your feet for attention.  Neither are big fans of being picked up and held, but they make up for it with the incredible amount of attention they will give you 'at ground level'. Since they both spent at least a few years fending for themselves on the streets, they are jumpy around new people, loud noises, and sudden unexpected movements, so they should go to a fairly quiet home without children. But once you've won their hearts (which is pretty easy with food and treats!), this cuddly duo will never leave you alone. 

They are both in great health, but Boots is FIV positive - a legacy of spending almost his entire life living on the streets. He adores indoor life, with its constant supply of attention, food, and toys, but endearingly still hasn't figured out how to drink out of a water bowl, after so many years of having to dip his paw into puddles to get water! Both Little Miss Sunshine and Boots love other cats - especially Boots, who is built like a tank, but has the heart of a teddy bear and the mew of a kitten. Little Miss Sunshine and Boots are a heartwarming and wonderful pair of cats, and watching them together is guaranteed to bring a smile on even the darkest day. Don't believe us? Click Play above to watch their video Will these lovebirds find their forever home with you?

Tony and Caesar came from a feral cat colony as kittens and were soon placed in a home where they were loved and allowed to adjust to indoor life at their own pace. They were in their new home for two years until their human became suddenly ill and had to be hospitalized. They are now in a foster home waiting for their forever home.
 
The boys still show signs of nervousness and are skittish but they are also gentle, affectionate and enjoy human companionship. They initially hid and were frightened in their foster home but have made remarkable progress in the past two months. Caesar meows and greets his foster mom for strokes and belly rubs and follows her around. When approached too quickly, he will dart away, but he quickly returns to seek attention. Tony also loves to be stroked and patted but he also still spends some time hiding. However, when his foster mom sits on the bed, he jumps up to seek attention and snuggle beside her.
 
The boys are bonded and play together, chasing each other up and down the hallway of their foster home. They seem to get along well with other cats as they are curious about the resident kitties in their foster home, even if they get chased or hissed at. They are so good-natured. They donât hiss, swat or bite, not even when frightened. When at the vet clinic, they were frightened but tolerated being examined and having their nails trimmed. We are not sure how they would get along with a dog. They are very easy-going despite being skittish so they could be okay with a gentle, friendly dog who likes cats.
 
They lived harmoniously with one older child in their first home. Because of their skittishness, they would be best in a quiet home. They need an experienced and understanding guardian who will wait for them to come out of their shell at their own pace. Once familiar with their new person, they will be interactive, expressive and affectionate, though they will still likely hide when visitors drop in, but thatâs not uncommon with any nervous cat.
 
They are three years of age and healthy, up to date with shots and microchipped. They are indoor cats which would be best given their nervous nature.

Scout is a sweet 11 year old brown and white tabby.  She was rescued by construction workers who found her hiding in an abandoned house after the owner had passed away.  
Scout loves to be pet, and purrs with content.  She loves to play with her toys, and nap in her kitty bed.  One of her favourite toys is the cat dancer.  

Scout is a darling but takes time to adjust to new people. She would do best in a quiet, adult only home with no other pets.  She tends to get  stressed when there are more that 2 or 3 people around.  

Scout is diabetic and currently receives two small doses of insulin daily, but the vet is hopeful  it will eventually be able to be controlled with a prescription diet.  

Scout is looking forward to meeting you!

Tessa is a former semi-feral kitty who had a rough beginning. She was found on the streets with her kittens, fending for herself for the first 5 years of her life. When she was found, her trapper noticed she had a severe infection in her mouth that required immediate attention. 

Tessa was taken to the vet, who discovered she had one of the most severe mouth infections he had ever seen. The only solution to heal her was to remove all of her teeth except for 2. After her surgery, Tessa went to an experienced socialization foster home. Afraid of people and in pain, Tessa hissed and was afraid of humans for the first month of her stay. She then developed a skin infection as she licked her fur and the infection of her mouth wasn't going away. Tessa was then taken to the vet and had her last 2 teeth removed, and over the course of a month her skin infection all cleared up and she started to become a noticeably relieved and happy kitty.

Free from pain and with lots of TLC, Tessa started coming around. She played for the first time. She purred for the first time. She let her foster mom pet her for the first time. Before we knew it, Tessa was jumping around chasing the laser, playing with mice, interacting with other indoor kitties and coming out of hiding to accept snuggles and pets from her foster mom. Even to the point of sitting up on the couch on occasion! 

Nowadays Tessa loves chasing the laser, chasing strings that her human dangles, receiving snuggles in her own way (not all day long, but yes she likes petting and purrs), rolling around on her back on her favourite bed and she is very playful overall. Several times a day her foster mom will catch her attacking a toy mouse in the hallway. She doesn't let having no teeth stop her from anything! She can eat dry and food and her new home must give her 1 pill 2x a week (easily dropped into a bowl of wet food). 

She can be afraid and worrisome around female cats, or cats with big personalities. Tessa would do best with a gentler, docile male cat (where she feels comfortable to be her big personality self). She should go to a home without dogs or small children as sudden movements scare her. She takes a while to get used to people and must be introduced to a new home gradually, in steps. It'd be ideal for her potential future adopter to visit the foster home several times to bond before bringing her home. Tessa's new home should be pretty quiet, without any easy 'exits' back to the outdoors, such as doors open to the street. 

Tessa is such a treat. She is spunky, playful and has a big personality. This is one happy-tail story of a semi-feral cat being rescued off the street, saved and loved to become a happy indoor kitty. Tessa is living the good life now and will make anyone a happy and lucky human.

Eve is a sweet 11 month old tabby who is bonded to her sister Rachel. They would love to find a home together. Eve is a sweet, shy girl with beautiful blue-green eyes, who will take a while to get comfortable in new surroundings. She loves food, and comes around to her foster mom, begging for treats. 

Eve loves relaxing in the sun beams, and playing while her foster mom is in the room. She loves to be pet during meal times. She's not a lap cat, but will sometimes sit on the other end of the couch with you while you read or watch TV. 

Loud sudden noises can make her nervous and send her off running to hide, so she would do best in a quiet home with no young kids. 

Rachel and Eve are very cute together, and entertaining to watch. Contact Annex Cat Rescue to meet these adorable kitties.

Rachel is a sweet tortoiseshell 11 month old kitty who is bonded to her sister Eve. She would love to be adopted together with her. Rachel is a super curious playful klutz. Her crazy tortoise shell markings show her clown personality. She is not always the most graceful cat, slipping off her perches or diving for a toy. She wants to see everything, check every nook and cranny, and she is smart, good at opening drawers and doors! She loves her toys and carries them around. She always wants to know what you are doing and will follow you around and check the places you've been. She's alway stealing the dog's bed. She has had some skin problems that were cleared up with antibiotics and she is on a special diet of Hill's d/d. She also gets the odd sore on her lip which may require medication.

Rachel can be a bit nervous around loud sudden noises or movement, so would do best in a calm household with no young kids. 

Rachel and Eve are very cute together, and entertaining to watch. Contact Annex Cat Rescue to meet them.

Herbert is a sweet 10 year old ginger domestic short hair. He is timid and gentle, purring readily and will now approach and sit on at least half a lap to be petted and fussed over! Herbert's little "curly" ears make his sweet little face extra adorable. He would do well in an only-cat home, without small children, as he is somewhat nervous around other pets, and will run and hide at loud noises and sudden movements. He enjoys napping in a quiet spot until he gets munchy again and ventures out for food and attention. Herbert has hyperthyroidism and needs to have a pill twice a day, which we follow up with lots of affection! He will make a gentle and purry addition for a quiet home where he will get many snuggles and lots of attention.

Kylo is a calm kitty with gorgeous eyes.  She can be quite shy. She takes time to get to know new humans and new places, but once she is familiar,  she is very affectionate.  

Kylo looks almost identical to her sister Mavis. She  graciously allows her sister Mavis to take daring risks, cautiously observing, and acting when she feels its safe to do so. 

Kylo and Mavis share a very strong bond. They call to each other from opposite ends of the house, play together, and groom each other. They would love to be adopted together into a loving and calm home.

Miss Mavis loves her humans.  She's up as soon as someone else is up in the house, following every step, and demanding attention.  Mavis is adventurous and playful, loves to chase objects, and does not give up easily.  

Mavis is bonded to her sister Kylo, and they need to be adopted together.  The two of them make an amazing pair, and should remain together.  It is very entertaining to watch them play together and groom each other.

Contact Annex Cat Rescue today to meet Mavis and her sister Kylo.

Simba is a sweet, trusting  FIV+ 3 year old cat with a lot of love to give.  Simba loves to cuddle and is very affectionate and social. He also can be chatty, and  likes to have a conversation with you.  If you meow at him, he will respond to you with a meow of his own.

When Simba wants attention and pets, he will nuzzle you to let you know.  Simba just LOVES play time.  He gets along well with other cats.  Simba can't wait to meet you! Contact Annex Cat Rescue today.

Frodo is a gorgeous three year old medium haired brown tabby.  He was rescued as a stray  from the street. Frodo can be shy when meeting new people.  Once he gets to know you, he is a lot of fun to have around. Frodo enjoys head rubs, being brushed and exploring cupboards.  

Frodo is an  escape artist extraordinaire - he has twice escaped from his previous foster home and needed to be retrapped requiring considerable time and effort. If a window is open even a fraction for any length of time he WILL open it and break the screen out and escape.  For his own safety, he can only be adopted into an extremely secure home - he would be perfect for a new condo (no random holes in the wall behind appliances and in cupboards like older buildings), with no balcony and windows that don't open.

Contact Annex Cat Rescue to meet this sweet kitty!

Hello, I'm Marla. I enjoy playing with strings, paper balls taped on shoelaces, napping on my pillow, looking out the window, being pet and little kisses on my nose. I was abandoned because my family member was allergic to me so I am looking for a new forever home. I love to be in the same room as my foster parents, and prefer to be the only cat in the home. When you feed me wet food I get so excited I make the most delightful and adorable meowing sounds. I'm quiet at night because I know humans need their cat naps, too. If you let me I will visit you in your bed to purr and snuggle with you before settling to sleep on my own.

lm aka Little Bean, so named as she is a tiny girl, is a quiet, sweet and calm young girl. At the tender age of 1 she weighs in at just under 5 lbs due to a heart condition, tetralogy of fallot. Though calm and quiet, she still likes to play at her own pace and knows when it is time for her to slow down and take a rest. 

Bean likes to hang out with her people but is also happy to go off on her own and sleep the afternoon away in a sunbeam. She likes head scratches and back rubs throughout the day and evening but is not a needy girl. She also likes to curl up at the end of your bed for a good night's sleep.

Bean would do best in a quiet, calm home with no small children due to her condition. She has never lived without another cat in her life so would be best suited in a home with another calm and friendly cat.

Bean's heart defect will need to be monitored regularly by a vet. At this time, she does not need any medications. She will eventually develop chronic heart failure in roughly three to six years from her heart defect, but is currently healthy. Her life expectancy is roughly four to eight years.

At the moment, Bean's treatment plan involves a blood test every 6 months and a yearly recheck with the cardiologist. This plan will likely change in the future as the disease progresses and Bean requires more frequent exams and/or medication.

Bean is so sweet and will be a wonderful companion. Contact Annex Cat Rescue today to meet her.

Nike is a boisterous fella who likes nothing more than to hang around with his human owner. He enjoys lots of attention, whether energetic playtime with the cat wand, or strokes around his ears. Bring out the cat brush and his purrs can be heard immediately. If he doesn't get your attention he's not shy about following you around the house and asking for it. 

Nike had been living on the streets for two years, and despite his friendly and out-going nature, he's still shy in new company and takes time to acclimatize to strangers. Once he knows you, he'll adore spending time with you.  Nike doesn't get along with other cats and needs to be the only pet in the home. He has't been around kids before, but he has the potential to be a great family cat.  

Nike is most energetic at night. He likes to tuck you into bed, enjoy a cuddle on your chest, and then he's off playing next door or warbling to himself. This is a cat that has lots of love to give, but needs the attention and time of his human companion.

Hello, my name is Danny I am a sweet, shy boy looking for a forever home with my buddy Larry.

I was found out in the country in the dead of winter, I was so cold and hungry.

My favorite things are playing with my buddy Larry, cat laser, cat wand, cat dancer, I love interactive play.  I have several stuffed mice that I like to carry around and bat around, and when I get tired of them, sometimes I like to put them in my water dish for safe keeping.  I also love sitting by the window on my cat tree, I like to watch the squirrel that visits sometimes.  I love Temptation treats, and will carefully take the treats from my foster momâs fingers.  I have just recently been able to enjoy a few pets during this time.  I am a bit of a talker, and I talk to Larry all the time, he is the quiet type, and doesnât talk back, but I know he understands me.  
My foster mom says I am a delightful, entertaining cat.  I am still shy around people and will need a very compassionate, understanding and, patient home but I know, with the right new home I can shine.

Hello, my name is Larry, I am a sweet, shy, FIV+  big boy looking for a forever home with my buddy Danny.

I lived on the streets for a long time, I was lucky to find a very nice ladyâs house who would feed me and built me a shelter on her porch.  I was too afraid to go into her house at first, and wandered away and got hit by a car.  The streets of Toronto are a very scary and dangerous place.

My favorite things are playing with my buddy Danny, cat laser, and cat dancer, it takes me a bit longer to enjoy play, but I do love it.   I love Temptation treats, and will carefully take the treats from my foster momâs fingers.  This is a great time for pets, I love pets from my head to my tail, and am just getting used to getting brushed.  I love pets behind my ears, my cheeks and donât forget underneath my chin, heavenly.   

My foster mom says I am a big sweetie, and will need a very compassionate, understanding and, patient home, where my light can shine.

Hi, I'm Sebastian and I am the only kitty left at my foster mom's as my brothers and sister have been adopted. Which is good because I was very shy when they were around but now that they are gone I can come out of my shell. I am still a little frightened of loud noises but I just love to snuggle and pet. I lure my foster mom into 'my bedroom' for treats and then snuggle in for lots of love. I don't love being picked up but I will tolerate it so that you can cuddle me. At the ripe old age of 1 I am still playful but have outgrown that 'kitten stage'.  I am FIV+ but am otherwise very healthy.  I am good with other cats but would do best in a home with older children as my environment would be a little quieter. If you are interested in letting me into your heart and your home, please contact an Annex volunteer.

Kahlua is a tiny 1 year old tortie who of course carries a bit of that tortie attitude.  She will often growl gently at new people while rubbing your leg for pets and purring! Kahlua is an independent girl who loves to chase her mouse, her ball or just sit in her tunnel and paw at her hanging toys. She also loves afternoon naps and flopping on the floor for head rubs and chin scratches. Kahlua is a big fan of laying in sunbeams and getting her back petted as well.  She can be shy with new people but doesn't take long to warm up once she knows how much you love her and her little white chin.  Kahlua would like to be adopted with her sister Mimosa but is fine with friendly cats.  If Kahlua sounds like the girl that belongs with your family, please contact an Annex volunteer.

Mimosa  is a petite little 1 year old  girl who bears a striking resemblance to ET.  This friendly little moppet likes to be pet, likes to hop in bed with you for a love session and a good night's sleep and is easy to pick up though she doesn't appreciate being held so much.  Mimosa is playful and likes to play with her wand toy until she is worn out and needs her head scratched.  Mimosa would like to be adopted with her sister Kahlua but she is fine with any other friendly cat.  She just gets shy with them until she is comfortable.  Mimosa can also be shy with strangers but once she warms up to her people, she is right there with you. 
If you are interested in bringing Mimosa into your heart and your home, please contact an Annex volunteer.

Bella is a quiet and affectionate kitten. She is gentle and a bit shy, but will turn into a lap snuggler all day long if she's given a chance. She would enjoy a laid-back environment and thrives with loving attention. She likes to chase her string toy, sit in baskets and boxes, and she can either be adopted with her outgoing sister Pebbles, on her own, or as a companion to a mellow or older resident cat.

Smokey was rescued after being found abandoned in an apartment. Despite his past trauma, he is an affectionate and loving cat, looking for his forever home!

Smokey is an incredibly playful cat. He loves toys that he can chase and pounce (like the Cat Dancer toy). He is totally not fooled by a laser pointer, and doesnât really âgetâ a lot of puzzle toys, but will happily chase any bit of ribbon you dangle.

Smokeyâs favourite thing by far is snuggling. While heâs not much of a lap cat and doesnât love being picked up, donât be surprised to find this ball of fur pressed up next to you in bed or on the couch!

While getting used to a new home, the most important this is to build trust with Smokey. Donât be surprised if he stakes out a piece of furniture to hide under and claims it as his territory! But after a few days of play, patience and spoiling him with treats, heâll soon feel comfortable enough to sprawl out in the middle of the floor, or on a perch where he can do some window-watching. It's also a good idea to give him space while he gets used to you, but - trust me! - soon he'll be wanting to spend time with you all day!

Smokey isn't a fan of being put in his carrier, so it's best that his forever home leaves the carrier out at all times, almost like a cat bed with a blanket inside, and try to encourage him to go in occasionally with cat nip, toys and treats. That way, when you do have to put him in the carrier for visits to the vet, it'll be easier to get him in.

When it comes to trimming his claws, his foster mom finds that the best method is to get him to lie in bed with you, and then gently trim them, one paw at a time, and let him dictate when he wants to stop.. 

Smokey needs a patient experienced adopter. It will take him a bit to feel comfortable in his new home. He might hide under some furniture while he gets used to a new person, and may be a bit grumpy. While Smokey is getting used to his new home, it's a good idea to wear slippers inside the home, as the heavy tread of shoes makes him nervous. Despite his dislike of change in environment, he will settle in fairly quickly. It only took him three days in his new foster home to be comfortable. 

Smokey takes a daily medication to help his anxiety levels. He would do best in a home with no small children, and no other pets in the home.

Pebbles is an outgoing kitten who will follow you around, keeping tabs on what you are doing. Everything is a game to her, she loves to play all day long and will inspect the sink and bathtub for splashing.  She also likes being picked up and carried on your shoulder. She has a great time with her sister Bella and can be adopted with her, as a friend to another cat, or on her own. She is easy-going and patient with kids, and not easily fazed by a noisy environment.

Phoenix is only 3 months old and very sweet. She is black and white with pink nose and paws. She loves to be held and will purr loudly when pet and loves to cuddle. Jersey loves to play with a wand and is very good with other cats. This little girl likes to roll around on the bed and rub her face into yours. She is playful but bites sometimes when playing so probably would not do best with small children. Phoenix is bonded to her brother, Jersey, and they should be adopted together.

Jersey is all black with very personable green eyes. He loves to cuddle and purrs load like an engine. He is only 3 months old but is tall for his age so he will grow to be a large cat. He loves to play with toys and is very good with other cats. He loves to be held and sleeps in the bed with you. He will wake you up just to rub his face against yours and have you run his belly. Jersey is a wonderful cat. He would likely do well in an active household. Jersey is bonded to his sister Phoenix, and they should be adopted together.

Hawthorne is a tiny tabby who doesnât let her size stand in her way.  She loves to chat and purrs up a storm.  Sheâs a perfect combo of cuddly and playful!  Hawthorne would be happy to go to a home with another friendly cat to play with.

Hazel is a tiny tabby cat who raised four beautiful kittens.  Now that they are weaned it's Hazel's turn to find her forever home.   Hazel was picked on by the other cats in her former home so she would prefer to be an only cat (although a very laid back male might be acceptable).

Hazel is sensitive, playful and affectionate once she gets to know her human companion.  She may need a little patience to come out of her shell, but once she gets past her fear she's a delightful little cat.

Meet Wimpy! Wimpy is a gorgeous long haired FIV+ orange tabby. Within the last few months of 2015, the members of ACR decided to search for Wimpy and pull him off the streets after he was noticeably losing weight and looking sickly. Wimpy was also hit by a car that left him with a broken femur. After 4 months of efforts, Wimpy was trapped on Christmas, and he soon found himself in the good hands of the caring and reliable folks over at a local vet clinic. He was later placed in a socialization foster home and really has come around. 


Wimpy loves attention (and food) and is there in the kitchen whenever his foster mom is. Once he knows you, he adores being pet, but he is nervous around new people. He seems to be more comfortable with women, and can be a bit shyer around men. He lives for the attention of other friendly male cats, he absolutely needs to be with at least one friendly male buddy - he spends his time head butting the male foster cats in his home, rubbing up against them, following them around. 

Wimpy is just starting to get used to being picked up and going onto a lap or shoulder while his foster mom is sitting on the floor. He needs a patient adopter comfortable with drawing shy former street cats out of their shell, but he is incredibly sweet and loves attention once he is used to you. 

Contact Annex Cat Rescue to meet Wimpy!

Roman is a sweet, affectionate FIV+ cat who loves nothing more than being petted (including treats)! Roman is happiest when he is spending time with you, especially if you're paying attention to him at the same time. He will follow you around and nuzzle you when he thinks it's time for you to pet him more. He would likely do well with another cat in the home. 

He is a relatively low-energy cat, who prefers being petted to playing. He would do best in a home without small children, as he sometimes will nip when he plays.

Roman can be a bit shy at the beginning, but give him some time to settle in and soon enough he won't leave your side!

Meet friendly Frisco!!  He is a very handsome, energetic guy with a long slinky body and a âbig personalityâ.  

He is full of vim and vigor and races around a room like he owns it â his antics will make you laugh out loud!!

He loves to be cuddled and stroked and will purr immediately when touched!!!  And he does not mind being picked up or handled in any way.  He always wants to be the centre of attention and uses a delightful little squeak to get you to notice him!! 
  
Frisco would love to be adopted into a home with another young and playful feline as he loves to rough-house with his two siblings.  He has never met a dog so we are not sure about that but would consider it.

This very loving, playful fellow would be a wonderful and rewarding addition to your life.

Meet our little black beauty Dakota!!  She is a very quiet and calm little one.  

She is shy with people at first, but will warm up to you with gentle stroking.

She loves to cuddle and will stretch out and lie right up against your side and purr contentedly.  She purrs almost immediately when touched!!!  And once she is familiar with you, she enjoys being picked up and cuddled.  
  
Dakota would do best in a quiet home with no young children or dogs.  She enjoys the companionship of her two siblings and would love a gentle feline playmate.

This very sweet and gentle little girl would be a wonderful and rewarding addition to your life.

Meet Maui!!  A beautiful, sweet and loving black beauty!!  

She is playful and loves to dart in and around her scratching post.  Although she can be a little shy at first, she loves to be cuddled and stroked, and will purr almost immediately when touched!!!  And she does not mind being picked up.  

If you lie down with her, she will stretch out and press her little body along your side and purr her head off.
  
Maui would do best in a home with no young children or dogs.  She loves to play with her two siblings and would adore to be adopted into a home with another young and playful feline.

This very loving, playful girl would be a wonderful and rewarding addition to your life.

Jaime is just over a year old.  He is a beautiful medium haired tabby with yellow eyes and orange white and black strips. Jamie wants your attention all day and night. He loves to be pet, rubbed down and scratched behind his head and on his hind. He loves playing with wand toys and chasing and catching treats (through him around the house). He also enjoys belly rubs and getting in boxes and bags.

Jamie gets along well other cats. He loves to sleep on the bed and relax by the window smelling fresh air though the screen.  He enjoys a calm household so probably would not do best with kids. Jaime was extremely scared when he first moved to his first foster home and will swat if approached too fast. He does not like to be held but will let you pet him till the sun goes down. It takes a while to earn his trust but so worth it when he finally shows you how much love he has in return for you.

Pine is a relaxed and calm boy who loves people, cats and afternoon naps. Pine loves a good neck rub, chin rub and back rub and is happy to sleep with you every night. He also wouldn't mind if you cuddled up for an afternoon nap with him, and really who wouldn't love a great reason for a nap! He is just an affectionate, chill 2 year old who is more into his chillaxing stage and out of his kitten years.  Pine is quite fond of other cats and would probably not be happy as an only. He currently resides with his 4 siblings, Spruce, Mimosa, Kahlua and Elm as well as a wee kitten named Aurelia,  all of whom he gets along with famously. Pine would do best in a home with older respectful children. If you think this sweet boy could make a wonderful addition to your family, please contact an Annex volunteer.

*available for pre-adoption only, pending spay/vaccination/microchipping*

Wynken is a playful little scamp rescued from a feral colony is Scarborough along with her sister Blynken and her brother Nod. She likes to run if you try to pick her up but upon being caught will purr almost immediately and settle in for a snuggle. Her favourite pastimes include tussling with her brother and sister, climbing anything in sight which includes but is not limited to cat trees, bookshelves, TVs, rolled up rugs and mantels. She would love to be adopted together with one of her siblings, or into a home where there is another kitty for her to play with.

Blynken would love to be adopted together with one of her siblings, or into a home where there is another kitty for her to play with.

Nod is an adorable kitten who has really blossomed since being brought indoors. He's the most curious of his three siblings and can sometimes be found adventuring around on his own. He loves to chase around the cat dancer toy with feathers on the end until he gets completely exhausted. His favourite nap spots include, the warm place behind the tv and cable box, a kitten hammock that he likes to suckle on and his new spot on the cat tree. Nod would love to be adopted together with one of his siblings or into a home where there's another cat for him to play with.

Randy is a fine and dandy kitten rescued from a colony. His tiger stripes gives him the confidence in thinking he may just be one giving a human the tiniest hiss before melting in your arms. He already has no problems in being handled and will allow pets for as long as you do. The perfect lap cat cuddle monster in training.

He is currently rooming with his Uncle Bandit, shadowing his every move and learning his manners so he can take a his best paw forward as a proper gentlecat for his future forever caretaker.

Biscuit is an adorable 3 month old kitten who is very calm. He purrs frequently and is a very content kitty.  He could win the best sleeper award! Biscuit would be an ideal friend for those who like routine, especially when it comes to winding down!  He's a very stretchy boy, so the best bed for him would be extra-long. Jesse is an adorable FIV+  4  year old grey  tabby kitty. He loves to 'lounge" most of the day, generally somewhere close to where his human companions are. Winter is coming... and he's looking for his furever home!

Winter arrived with his tiny sister Autumn and they have officially been put on "purr patrol" due to their exceptional rumble. With his adorable white mitts, you can tell that Winter is going to grow into an impressive cat. He has boundless energy and loves to play, zipping around the apartment and attacking the scratching post. He also loves wand toys and will chase a piece of string for hours of fun.

His namesake season may be known for snow, but this Winter loves playing in water. He's even joined his foster family in the shower once! If you fill the sink with an inch of water, he'll happily splash around if you don't mind a mess.

Winter would love to be adopted with his petite sister Autumn, but also gets along well with other cats. He's been happy to play with his foster family's adult tabby and is good at setting boundaries.

Fall in love with Autumn "on this harvest moon."

Autumn is petite, lovely, and a purr-fect lady. She enjoys sleeping at the foot of the bed (sometimes even tucking herself under the covers!) and has no issue being held or brushed. Hemingway had a rough start after being diagnosed with FIV - but that doesn't stop him from being lovable and affectionate. Ten-year-old Harry came to ACR via one of our volunteers. He previously had a family so he is well-socialized and loves people. He does not like other pets though and would be best suited to a household where he alone is the centre of attention
.

Kiwi was born on the mean streets but she couldn't be more sweet! She purrs loudly with excitement at the arrival of a new friend or toy and is interested in everything! She's fond of belly rubs and head scratches and has already made herself at home, getting cozy on her foster mom's bed at night. She's fond of other kitties and would like to be adopted into a home with another cat to keep her company. Everything is more fun with two (or three)!

Casper is  a self confident, cheeky, curious kitten.  If you open any cupboard or drawer Casper is in there immediately.  He is the leader of the pack.  Casper would be fine in a home with slightly older children.  

Casper loves to play and sleep on the top of the scratching post. He purrs like a motor boat.  He is a real lap cat and likes to sleep near his foster mom throughout the night. He is slowly being introduced to the resident dog, and things are going well.  

Casper can be timid around people he's just met, but likely will bond with his new family right away. 

Casper would be delighted to be adopted into a home that has another kitty there for him to play with.

Spring is a gorgeous grey tabby kitten. She will take some time to warm up to you, but once she feels comfortable in her new home, you'll have a sweet cuddly friend for life. There's nothing she love more than a quick cuddle between wrestling matches with her BFF Summer. Spring is also very curious about adult cats, and will adjust well to an older brother or sister. Spring's most favourite things are climbing up the cat tower like a baby monkey, wet food and watching nature documentaries on Netflix (especially ones with fish!)

Summer is a fluffy little cuddle monster. She quickly adapts to her new surroundings and people, poking her tiny pink nose into anything she can find. Summer loves being picked up and cuddled, and will let you know she's happy by flopping into you for a nuzzle. Summer is a very good friend to other kitties, especially her BFF Spring, who she loves to play and snuggle with. Summer's favourite things are cuddles, catnip toys and sleeping in odd places.

Jake is a very loving and sweet tempered boy.  He is very energetic and adaptable. He loves to romp and play with his sister Maggie.  He is totally accepting of his surroundings and isn't fazed by any household activities.  He is always ready to engage with you and purrs whenever he sees you. He does not make strange with anyone.  When it is bedtime, he loves nothing more than to be cuddled in with his sister in the top of the cat tree.  They both love to be kissed good night and enjoy being shown affection.  He would be best suited for adoption with his sister. There's a lot of energy between the two of them and they would keep each other entertained.

Maggie is an engaging and affectionate little girl who loves to gaze into your eyes and steal your heart.  She plays energetically with her brother Jake.  She easily adapts to changing surroundings and is accepting of all who have handled her.  She shares her brother's loud purr and his fondness for cuddling up in the top of the cat tree. She very much enjoys being shown affection and like her brother enjoys being kissed good night. She would be best suited for adoption with her brother Jake There is a lot of energy between them and they would keep each other entertained.

Nigel is a shy kitty  who has been making progress with coming out of his shell.   Heâs still very young and is otherwise a darling: playful, eats well, uses the litter box faithfully, gets along well with others. He doesnât like being picked up but will come snuggle with you during the night , while purring away. While he is lounging around relaxing, he will let you pet him, especially in the evening hours and especially if he gets to lay on your bed. 

Nigel is interested in treats and catnip. If you are very patient and would like to experience the trials and rewards of building a trusting relationship with an ex-feral â or if youâre looking for second cat (heâd do well with a nice ârole modelâ cat)â letâs talk about Nigel.

Hope is a sweet girl with a big purr. She came from a home with many other cats who made her quite a scaredy-cat. She would do best in a home where she is the only pet.

Hope is quiet and very good - no scratching, litter accidents or plant eating while with her foster parents! She does startle easily but has become more and more confident and comfortable everyday. She'll take time to feel comfortable in her new home and will likely hide for quite a while. Not to fret, she will come around and then can be coaxed out easily to return to hanging out on the couch:)

Because of her timid history she'll need some strong encouragement to eat at first. Eventually she will eat on her own and show you the big purrs and licks she shares with her foster parents!

She will tolerate being picked up if needed and loves being pet and brushed. Hope is a quiet lovely little lady who would be a cute and kind addition to any home.

Willow is a darling, shy calico kitten. She was rescued from a feral colony and would do best in a quiet home with a patient adopter who is experienced with timid kitties. Willow loves playtime with her sister Stardust. She doesn't enjoy being held at first, but eventually relaxes. Willow adores being rubbed under her chin.

Willow has been around adult cats and dogs and gets along fine with them. She would love to be adopted into a home where there is another cat for her to play with, or together with her sister Stardust.

Stardust is a stunning, inquisitive black and white kitten who was rescued from a feral colony with her sister Willow. She loves playtime. Stardust does sometimes run and hides when her foster mom comes into the room, but comes right back out. She is getting braver every day. Stardust loves to cuddle, and purrs with content.

Stardust has been around adult cats and dogs and gets along well with them. She would love to find a home where there is another kitty for her to play with, or be adopted together with her sister Willow.
Please note that all kittens aged 6 months or under must be adopted in pairs or go to a home with another young cat to play with.

Meet sweet Daphne! She is kid tested and approved... a very sweet and loving 5 year old that just adores being near you and is happiest when sheâs receiving chin scratches and belly rubs. 

She gets along with pretty much everyone. She is not, however, a fan of the vacuum. As with most cats, one glimpse of it and itâs a hiss and off she goes! She returns once the coast is clear of course â then itâs back to chin scratches and belly rubs! Sheâs a little on the chunky side, and has been losing weight since coming into the rescue. 

Daphne would make a great addition to a house with other cats and/or kids. Sheâs not been tested with dogs, but given her quiet and gentle demeanor, with the right introductions, sheâd probably do well with a canine companion. 

If you're interested in welcoming this gentle addition into your family, please email info@teamcatrescue.ca today!

THE KISSING BANDIT: Shadow joined our rescue last week (more on that here: http://bit.ly/2anjWYy) all the way from North Carolina, now residing in Toronto, and we have a problem. A big problem. We had no idea we were welcoming a canine with his kind of experience into our care, we were ill prepared and taken aback at his behavior. You see, it appears that Shadow has mastered the art of kissing and goes to great pains to ensure that all those within close personal range receive either a hug or a kiss, we have tried reasoning with him, but he insists its welcome attention and he has been conducting himself in this fashion for the last 5 years of his life and has always worked for him in the past, he has no idea how he wound up in a shelter with him being such a Casanova and all, but he is grateful for the opportunity to come to Toronto and show Canadians how itâs done. Shadow also doesnât discriminate, he doesnât just shower the attention on the ladies, the men are not excluded from his lavish affections. Shadow is exceptionally playful, affectionate, sweet and energetic, however, his strength is in his kiss. 
If you are interested in learning more about Shadow please contact us at adopt@teamdogrescue.ca if you have been seeking a man like him your whole life.
Shadow is extraordinary.

Today we'd like to introduce you to Calle and Kaax, our special cats all the way from Mexico!

Hi! My name is Calle (the handsome tabby), and this my best friend Kaax. We're senior cats (at eight years young) and we've been through some rough times together, but we would love to make a new start with you. We were rescued by an amazing woman in Mexico, but devastatingly, she passed away. After some travel and sadness, we're now ready to find a furever home to settle in.

So, a bit about me! I love napping in the sun, investigating my surroundings and cuddling. I will curl up on your lap, snuggle next to you in bed and happily keep you company as you surf the net and binge watch the newest Netflix series. You should know that although I'm blind, it does not hold me back. You will never catch me bumping into your furniture as other cats strangely seem to do. I may be nervous in new places at first, but after some slow exploring, I will find the most comfortable perches in your home in no time!


Hey Calle, move over! It's my turn! I'm Kaax. Nice to meet you! Calle may be the more outgoing one, but once I warm up to you, I'm even snugglier than he is! I might keep my distance at first or hide a bit; however, soon I will venture out and rub my face up against your legs to let you know that I would love for you to pet me. If you sit on the couch, you are definitely fair game as far as I'm concerned... before you know it, I will have hopped up beside you, hoping it's cuddle time.

Once I get to know you, I will want to stay close to you. Kaax is a Mayan name which means guardian of all animals. I will always be there for you, and I don't want you to feel lonely ever again!

If you have never considered adopting a senior cat, you might want to think about it. Calle and I will give you so much love, without keeping you awake at night and jumping all over you the way kittens might. You'll know exactly what to expect from us! Most of all, you'd be giving us a new start to a big chapter in our lives, a chapter that's going to be full of love and lots of relaxation -- hopefully with you!

If you're looking for a pair of laid back cuddle bugs, wise with experience but young at heart, please go to teamcatrescue.ca and fill out an application or email info@teamcatrescue.ca

Oh hi friends! Happy Galentine's day! Kat here, dropping a line from the foster home I share with Audrey. My bff and I are looking forward to a great day of gallivanting together, with some treats and toys and a celebration of us and our special bond! Some might say we're in our golden years, although you would hardly know it to look at us - I'm around 14 myself, while Audrey (the pretty calico one) is a spry young 15.

Despite our winning personalities, our old owner saw fit to surrender us to a shelter, and well... let's just say we're so happy we have each other to rely on. Our foster home is great too but we can't wait to find our real forever home. I guess this is the place for me to mention that I was diagnosed with something called 'hyperthyroidism,' but all it really means is that I have a special kind of food I need to eat. It's no waffles and whipped cream, but fine, I will eat it if I must. Audrey and I have very refined tastes if you can't already tell!

I am really pretty confident we will keep you entertained all day long. I especially am a bit of an adventurer, and love checking out my surroundings and finding new areas to explore. Give Audrey a crinkly cat toy and she will go nuts! In between our shenanigans, we're super happy to purr up a storm for you and give you all the love and appreciation we have for offering us our new home. We are definitely not a huge fan of dogs, and we haven't met too many other cats or kids but really, our focus right now is just on staying together.

In honour of Galentine's day (actually, technically in honour of Valentine's day, but who needs that when you have a strong sisterly bond?!), Team is offering a special offer on adopting us for $100. So really, the time has never been better - just email info@teamcatrescue.ca and they'll hook you up. We can't wait to join your waffle breakfast and gab like real gal (or guy!) pals!

Kneesa and Padme are two beautiful Princesses looking for love! These strong-willed beauties can seem a tad aloof and haughty when you first meet them (as any royalty should rightly be) but once you gain their trust, they will show you their playful side.

Kneesa, from the wilds like the Wookie of her name, is an outspoken grey lady and will battle with your finest mice down to your most unruly crinkly balls. Padme, bonded with Kneesa, though not as eloquent, will be the first to offer peace terms as long as food is part of the deal. She is a beautiful tabby, the mother of kittens Luke and Leia, and will only deign to single combat with the most regal of opponents: the feather-wand.

In celebration of Valentine's Day, we're offering a special rate of $100 for our bonded pairs. So, if you're interested in adopting these two royal beauties, please email info@teamcatrescue.ca -- they will gladly keep you company at the throne in your own home for many years to come!

Ooof! Oh, hi there! Didn't see you coming up behind me. A few months ago, that would have made me nervous, but I'm becoming quite the independent little kitty... getting more and more adventureous, just like my namesake. Wait, how rude of me... my name is Han, and I am the cat alter-ego to the Great Space Explorer, Han Solo! (I am also the fuzzy guy pictured below!) We are both curious and great scavengers... I use my wits to protect my dad, Wicket. Just like the great Chief Ewok, Wicket Wystri Warrick, he can be a tad guarded and reserved. (He is the short-haired cutie.) You see, we spent much of our time together fending for ourselves out there in the galaxy before coming into Team Cat Rescue's foster program. He doted on me and kept me safe, but now that I'm bigger, it's my turn to help my dad learn to trust again. But Dad sure does like to watch you human-folk... I think he gets that curiousity from his days as the Chief of the Mean Streets -- we had a hard life among the planets, you know! But now, he even enjoys being pet on the head. He'll venture round the planet of Foster Home with me, but only if I lead the way.

For Valentine's Day, a holiday you humans use to celebrate love and bonding, Team Cat Rescue is offering a special rate of $100 for bonded pairs in February. Wow! What a steal! You couldn't even buy the The Millennium Falcon with that. Wicket is dependent on me; I guide him and keep him company while we work towards building up our confidence. We would like to find our special Wookie friend or family to hunker down with for the rest of time. We can explore your home together, curl up and watch TV, and I'll keep you safe from the Dark Side aka this long dreary winter. We would love to be a part of your family and grow with you so that we can become the strongest warrior cuddle buddies in the universe. Do you have a Wookie home for us?

If you're interested in meeting us, please email info@teamcatrescue.ca!

Describing Daisy is the equivalent of describing your favorite person, how is it even possible to describe someone you love and admire most?  Daisy is beyond sweet, exceptionally entertaining, an expert cuddler that prefers to be in your arms more than anywhere else in the world, she is lively and fun, she has a zest for life that is unmistakable. Daisy loves human companionship and is more than just a lap dog, she wants to be close and near at all times, a retiree, or someone who is home more often than not would be in for a treat.

Daisy is everything, and so much more.
